			<div class="blog-faq"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the most effective treatment for a double chin?</h3>
					<p>The most effective treatment depends on the severity of the submental fullness and skin laxity. Liposuction provides excellent results for fat removal, while a neck lift addresses both fat and loose skin. Non-surgical options like Kybella and CoolSculpting are ideal for mild to moderate cases with minimal downtime.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long do double chin removal results last?</h3>
					<p>Surgical results from liposuction and neck lifts are long-lasting, typically five to ten years or more. Non-surgical results from Kybella are permanent for the treated fat cells, while CoolSculpting results are also permanent. However, aging and weight fluctuations can affect overall results over time.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is double chin removal painful?</h3>
					<p>Surgical procedures are performed under anesthesia, so there is no pain during surgery. Post-operative discomfort is managed with prescribed medication. Non-surgical treatments may cause mild discomfort during the procedure, which subsides quickly, with minimal soreness afterward.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How many Kybella sessions are needed?</h3>
					<p>Most patients require two to four Kybella sessions, spaced four to six weeks apart, to achieve optimal results. The exact number depends on the amount of submental fat and the desired outcome. Dr. Johar will create a personalized treatment plan during your consultation.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can a double chin come back after treatment?</h3>
					<p>After surgical liposuction or Kybella, the removed or destroyed fat cells do not regenerate, so results are permanent for the treated area. However, significant weight gain can cause fat accumulation in other areas. Maintaining a stable weight helps preserve results long-term.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the downtime for double chin removal?</h3>
					<p>Non-surgical treatments like Kybella and CoolSculpting have minimal downtime, with most patients returning to normal activities immediately. Surgical options like liposuction require seven to ten days of recovery, while a neck lift may require two to three weeks before returning to work.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How much does double chin removal cost in India?</h3>
					<p>Costs vary by treatment: liposuction ranges from INR 80,000 to 2,00,000, neck lift from INR 1,00,000 to 2,50,000, and non-surgical options from INR 15,000 to 40,000 per session. Dr. Johar provides transparent pricing and discusses all options during your consultation.</p>
				</div>
